                    "short_description":  "A scenic island in Vembanad Lake known for its rich birdlife and serene natural beauty.",
                    "detailed":  "Pathiramanal, meaning \u0027Sands of Midnight\u0027, is a picturesque island located in the heart of Vembanad Lake. Historically, it was owned by a royal family before coming under government administration. The island is uninhabited and serves as a natural habitat for numerous migratory and endemic bird species. Over 90+ species have been recorded here. The island is accessible only by boat from either Alappuzha, Muhamma or Kumarakom, making it a peaceful escape for nature lovers, photographers, and birdwatchers."
